    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\r\n\r\nMouse is currently not supported on terminal. This could be patched in an easy way.\r\n\r\n### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nWe should provide an option \r\n\r\n    mouse_terminal=true\r\n\r\n100% mouse functionality require the next steps.\r\n\r\n## When terminal is focused\r\n```sh\r\n# Make the mouse behave like in a regular terminal\r\nset mouse=\"\"\r\nprintf \"\\x1b[?1000l\"\r\n```\r\n\r\n## Before a program is executed\r\n```sh\r\n# Enable mouse support for terminal programs\r\nset mouse=a\r\nprintf \"\\x1b[?1000h\"\r\n```\r\n## When the program ends\r\n```sh\r\n# Restore regular mouse behavior for the terminal\r\nset mouse=\"\"\r\nprintf \"\\x1b[?1000l\"\r\n```\r\n## When terminal is unfocused\r\n```sh\r\n# Restore regular mouse behavior for neovim\r\nset mouse=a|h|n  #   the value the user had  setted\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe should clarify in the docs that one requires to have TERM=xterm256color for this to work, which is used by most modern terminals.\r\n\r\nOptionally, we could add 2 more options to let the user set their own termcodes to use instead of the default \\x1b[?1000h and \\x1b[?1000l.",
